    "description": "A one-at-a-time sensitivity study varied impeller tip clearance from 0.1 mm to 0.5 mm and blood viscosity from 0.0025 to 0.0040 Pa·s across all five operating points. NIH showed a monotonic 18% increase with decreasing tip clearance and a 9% increase with increasing viscosity, confirming that the minimum-clearance, maximum-viscosity condition is the credible worst case for hemolysis and validating the COU decision boundary."
